Marinette Dupain-Ching, here is the--

267
00:11:57.920 --> 00:12:01.160
- Don't worry, I know the drill, flop clockwise.

268
00:12:01.160 --> 00:12:03.760
- Good luck, this film's gonna be a toughie.

269
00:12:03.760 --> 00:12:06.800
Oh, do you have any tips to make this easier?

270
00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:08.720
- Unfortunately, I'm not allowed to interfere

271
00:12:08.720 --> 00:12:10.300
with the timeline, I know.

272
00:12:10.300 --> 00:12:13.540
I know you'll be all right.

273
00:12:13.540 --> 00:12:26.580
- You can't stay like that, Juleel.

274
00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:28.620
I'll go get something to clean you up.

275
00:12:28.620 --> 00:12:30.080
Sorry, Plagg, picnic's over.

276
00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:32.420
- There wasn't a single piece of cheese anyway.

277
00:12:32.420 --> 00:12:34.920
The picnic might as well not even have started.

278
00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:36.220
- Plagg, claws out!

279
00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:39.520
- M'lady.

280
00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:49.200
- You think they're trying to get in for free?

281
00:12:49.200 --> 00:12:51.100
- I doubt they're fans of art.

282
00:12:51.100 --> 00:12:53.440
- They don't look like fans of ours, either.

283
00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:59.440
- It's nice of you to join this,

284
00:12:59.440 --> 00:13:01.140
but we'll tick the unguided tour.

285
00:13:01.140 --> 00:13:03.420
- Kata? - Careful, Kitty.

286
00:13:03.420 --> 00:13:04.620
You could hurt the Akumatai's villain

287
00:13:04.620 --> 00:13:05.760
if they turn out to be one of them.

288
00:13:05.760 --> 00:13:06.860
- You're right, m'lady.

289
00:13:06.860 --> 00:13:11.160
No one, may I?

290
00:13:11.160 --> 00:13:12.220
- Sure, Kitty.

291
00:13:12.220 --> 00:13:13.060
- Cataclysm.

292
00:13:13.060 --> 00:13:16.260
There's no Ultra Akuma in this one.

293
00:13:16.260 --> 00:13:18.960
- No one in here, either.

294
00:13:18.960 --> 00:13:27.840
- Come on, where's the Akumatai's villain?

295
00:13:27.840 --> 00:13:29.780
(evil laughter)

296
00:13:29.780 --> 00:13:31.780
- You'll never find me!

297
00:13:31.780 --> 00:13:33.580
- Sounds like it's coming from inside.

298
00:13:36.420 --> 00:13:39.180
- Whoever you are, just what are you trying to achieve?

299
00:13:39.180 --> 00:13:41.160
- Doing history justice.

300
00:13:41.160 --> 00:13:44.260
The Louvre must become a fortress, protecting Paris again,

301
00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:47.200
like Philip II of France had wanted.

302
00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:48.860
- You should brush up on your history.

303
00:13:48.860 --> 00:13:50.560
You're forgetting that the French Revolutionaries

304
00:13:50.560 --> 00:13:52.160
want to turn this castle into a museum

305
00:13:52.160 --> 00:13:54.040
so people could have access to art.

306
00:13:54.040 --> 00:13:57.400
- Decadent art that tarnishes the battles of monarchy.

307
00:13:57.400 --> 00:14:00.180
- More like art that upholds the values of democracy.

308
00:14:00.180 --> 00:14:02.080
- There is nothing you can do to stop

309
00:14:02.080 --> 00:14:04.140
the return of monarchy.

310
00:14:04.140 --> 00:14:07.140
- Stop the return of monarchy.

311
00:14:07.140 --> 00:14:08.280
- The Crown Gallery.

312
00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:10.420
- You're right, if the villain thinks he's a monarchy,

313
00:14:10.420 --> 00:14:11.420
he might be in there.

314
00:14:11.420 --> 00:14:15.020
- Try to stop the monarchy, it's above you.

315
00:14:15.020 --> 00:14:19.500
- Why try to keep us from getting in if the room's empty?

316
00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:21.840
- Since you enjoy the museum so much,

317
00:14:21.840 --> 00:14:25.340
how about becoming exhibits yourselves for eternity?

318
00:14:25.340 --> 00:14:30.300
- It's a trap!

319
00:14:30.300 --> 00:14:31.880
- Unleash Charm!

320
00:14:31.880 --> 00:14:33.780
- Cataclysm!

321
00:14:33.780 --> 00:14:35.640
- Come on, we've got to get out of here!

322
00:14:35.640 --> 00:14:51.820
- Okay, so he isn't hiding in the castle.

323
00:14:51.820 --> 00:14:54.200
- He is the castle!

324
00:14:54.200 --> 00:14:57.540
- I am the Dark Castle!

325
00:14:57.540 --> 00:15:01.440
And your magic will be no match for my power,

326
00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:05.200
the noble stone that founded history!

327
00:15:05.200 --> 00:15:13.780
- Milady, we could use some backup, don't you think?

328
00:15:13.780 --> 00:15:19.520
- No need for backup, we can do this on our own, kitty.

329
00:15:19.520 --> 00:15:20.360
- Whoa!

330
00:15:20.360 --> 00:15:26.660
- Your optimism never ceases to amaze me, Milady.

331
00:15:26.660 --> 00:15:28.600
- You'll never get Ladybug and Cat Noir

332
00:15:28.600 --> 00:15:31.260
to rally behind your noble cause, Dark Castle.

333
00:15:32.400 --> 00:15:34.460
- They deserve the fate reserved for traitors and rebels.

334
00:15:34.460 --> 00:15:35.900
But first.

335
00:15:35.900 --> 00:15:37.440
- Remember to seize their miraculous.

336
00:15:37.440 --> 00:15:46.720
- Missed me!

337
00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:48.220
- Can't get rid of a Ladybug that easy!

338
00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:05.600
- The museum's closing, please proceed to the nearest exit.

339
00:16:05.600 --> 00:16:15.240
- Cataclysm!

340
00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:28.520
- Milady, I think I found the akumatized object.

341
00:16:28.520 --> 00:16:31.920
- You'll never reduce the monarchy to ashes.

342
00:16:31.920 --> 00:16:41.740
- There!

343
00:16:41.740 --> 00:16:42.580
- Tary-ho!

344
00:16:58.520 --> 00:17:00.680
(panting)

345
00:17:00.680 --> 00:17:25.440
- How are we supposed to know where it'll reappear next?

346
00:17:25.440 --> 00:17:27.640
- You can't, without a great stroke of luck.

347
00:17:28.520 --> 00:17:29.760
- Lucky charm!

348
00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:38.160
- Are you suggesting a picnic, Milady?

349
00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:40.900
- No, I have another plan, a tight-up one.

350
00:17:40.900 --> 00:17:55.480
- You think you can start a revolution

351
00:17:55.480 --> 00:17:58.280
with a puny bit of string, you peasant?

352
00:17:58.820 --> 00:18:01.080
(grunting)

353
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:15.960
- The day of glory has arrived!

354
00:18:29.140 --> 00:18:31.180
- No more evil doing for you, Ultracouma.

355
00:18:31.180 --> 00:18:37.280
- Time to de-evilize!

356
00:18:37.280 --> 00:18:42.060
Gotcha!

357
00:18:42.060 --> 00:18:44.900
- Bye-bye, little butterfly.

358
00:18:44.900 --> 00:18:51.660
- Miraculous Ladybugs!

359
00:18:58.800 --> 00:19:01.180
(grunting)

360
00:19:01.180 --> 00:19:03.440
- Again with this vile pyramid,

361
00:19:03.440 --> 00:19:05.880
it's defacing this noble building

362
00:19:05.880 --> 00:19:08.720
that was once home to the French sovereigns.

363
00:19:08.720 --> 00:19:10.920
- Mr. Dajancourt, weren't the pyramids

364
00:19:10.920 --> 00:19:13.220
the last homes of the sovereigns of Egypt?

365
00:19:13.220 --> 00:19:16.700
- They were, indeed.

366
00:19:16.700 --> 00:19:18.060
You're right.

367
00:19:18.060 --> 00:19:24.400
- This jewel will remind you

368
00:19:24.400 --> 00:19:26.540
that we shouldn't rewrite past history,

369
00:19:26.540 --> 00:19:28.200
for it helps us to make the right decisions

370
00:19:28.200 --> 00:19:30.140
in shaping our future.

371
00:19:30.140 --> 00:19:31.540
- Thank you, Ladybug.

372
00:19:31.540 --> 00:19:34.740
You know, this pyramid isn't so ugly after all.

373
00:19:34.740 --> 00:19:37.480
- Count it!

374
00:19:37.480 --> 00:19:42.420
- Bunnynut, I'm done.

375
00:19:42.420 --> 00:19:44.860
- Counter-clockwise!

376
00:19:44.860 --> 00:19:46.920
- Good job, Ladybug.

377
00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:47.760
Thanks, Marinette.

378
00:19:47.760 --> 00:19:49.460
Fluff, Tiki, unify!

379
00:19:49.460 --> 00:19:56.460
At last, I can go to bed.

380
00:19:56.460 --> 00:19:57.740
- Thanks for your help.

381
00:19:57.740 --> 00:19:59.900
If you want something done, do it yourself.

382
00:19:59.900 --> 00:20:03.240
- She wasn't there.

383
00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:06.280
It goes to show, but I need to check again

384
00:20:06.280 --> 00:20:07.540
to make sure.

385
00:20:07.540 --> 00:20:10.180
Again, and again, and again.

386
00:20:10.180 --> 00:20:14.020
- So, how was your afternoon in the burrow?

387
00:20:14.020 --> 00:20:15.120
Not too boring?

388
00:20:15.120 --> 00:20:18.860
- No, not for a minute!

389
00:20:18.860 --> 00:20:20.260
Spots and lobs away.

390
00:20:20.260 --> 00:20:22.520
- You didn't miss the whole thing.

391
00:20:22.520 --> 00:20:23.900
I brought you back some cake.

392
00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:29.400
- Sorry about your surprise.

393
00:20:29.400 --> 00:20:30.400
It could have been better if--

394
00:20:30.400 --> 00:20:31.240
- Are you kidding?

395
00:20:31.240 --> 00:20:32.540
It was uber-awesome!

396
00:20:32.540 --> 00:20:34.740
The best birthday of my whole life!

397
00:20:34.740 --> 00:20:37.280
Thank you, Marinette, for real.

398
00:20:37.280 --> 00:20:40.280
- No, thank you for everything you do.

399
00:20:40.280 --> 00:20:42.240
Your mission is such a hard one.

400
00:20:42.240 --> 00:20:44.080
I can't make you do this anymore, Alex.

401
00:20:44.080 --> 00:20:46.380
Becoming bunnocks again, living away from your friends,

402
00:20:46.380 --> 00:20:48.660
just because I couldn't secure the butterfly miraculous,

403
00:20:48.660 --> 00:20:50.360
this isn't fair.

404
00:20:50.360 --> 00:20:52.560
It's my mistake, not yours.

405
00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:54.820
- Okay, you can keep the rabbit miraculous,

406
00:20:54.820 --> 00:20:56.960
but in exchange, you give me the Ladybug.

407
00:20:56.960 --> 00:21:01.100
- Huh, but I'm Ladybug, and I am bunnocks.

408
00:21:01.100 --> 00:21:04.000
And the best one there is.

409
00:21:04.000 --> 00:21:06.200
Happy birthday, bunnocks.

410
00:21:06.200 --> 00:21:07.400
Fluff Clockwise!

411
00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:15.620
- Oh, you told me that you were sick.

412
00:21:15.620 --> 00:21:17.180
I hope it's not too serious.

413
00:21:17.180 --> 00:21:19.020
When you wake up, let me know if you need anything,

414
00:21:19.020 --> 00:21:20.220
and I'll come right over.

415
00:21:20.220 --> 00:21:23.780
- Thanks, Adrian, I just woke up,

416
00:21:23.780 --> 00:21:25.660
and I think I'm still a bit contagious,

417
00:21:25.660 --> 00:21:28.560
but I super appreciate your message,

418
00:21:28.560 --> 00:21:30.300
and I'm sure that thanks to you,

419
00:21:30.300 --> 00:21:32.100
I'll feel 100% tomorrow morning.

420
00:21:32.100 --> 00:21:38.900
- So, how did the picnic go, sweetheart?

421
00:21:38.900 --> 00:21:41.400
- It went great, Dad, and the cake was delicious.

422
00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:51.220
- So, how did the picnic go, sweetheart?

423
00:21:51.220 --> 00:21:53.620
- It went great, Dad, and the cake was delicious.

424
00:21:55.820 --> 00:21:58.060
- Ugh, what a day.

425
00:21:58.060 --> 00:22:07.640
Three, two, one, and.

426
00:22:07.640 --> 00:22:11.240
Don't tell me you need me to guard the rabbit miraculous.

427
00:22:11.240 --> 00:22:12.240
- How did you know?

428
00:22:12.240 --> 00:22:14.000
- Well, I am you from the future.

429
00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:15.480
- Of course, makes sense.

430
00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:18.780
Thanks for your help.

431
00:22:18.780 --> 00:22:20.940
If you want something done, do it yourself.

432
00:22:20.940 --> 00:22:23.880
Pound it.

433
00:22:26.180 --> 00:22:28.580
(phone beeps)

434
00:22:28.580 --> 00:22:30.460
See you tomorrow morning, Marinette.

435
00:22:30.460 --> 00:22:31.300
I love you.

436
00:22:31.300 --> 00:22:34.320
- I love you, Adrian.

437
00:22:34.320 --> 00:22:35.520
See you tomorrow morning.
